## BucketList Card Spec

### Summary
The BucketList spec defines a card that allows users to manage a list of items, represented as a set of strings. It includes a header with the list name and the number of items, as well as a ChipsEditor component that lets users add, remove, and rearrange the list items.

### Import
```javascript
import { BucketList } from 'https://realms-staging.stack.cards/experiments/bucket-list';
```

### Usage as a Field
To use the BucketList card as a field within a consuming card or field, you can include it like this:

```javascript
import { CardDef, field, contains } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { BucketList } from 'https://realms-staging.stack.cards/experiments/bucket-list';

class MyCard extends CardDef {
  @field bucketList = contains(BucketList);
}
```

### Template Usage
To display the BucketList card within a consuming card or field, you can use the following template syntax:

```handlebars
<BucketList @model={{@fields.bucketList}} />
```

This will render the BucketList card using the data from the `bucketList` field.
